<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,867,952]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<typeStatus box="[151,201,868,892]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Bergh, 1880" authorityName="in Bergh" authorityYear="1880" box="[295,702,867,891]" class="Gastropoda" family="Discodorididae" genus="Hoplodoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="desmoparypha">
<emphasis box="[295,567,867,891]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Hoplodoris desmoparypha</emphasis>
Bergh, 1880
</taxonomicName>
. Formerly in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName authority="Abraham, 1877" authorityName="Abraham" authorityYear="1877" box="[1004,1336,867,891]" class="Gastropoda" family="Dorididae" genus="Doris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="raripilosa">
<emphasis box="[1004,1169,867,891]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Doris raripilosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Abraham, P. S." box="[1175,1336,867,891]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="196 - 269" refId="ref17137" refString="Abraham, P. S. (1877) Revision of the anthobranchiate nudibranchiate Mollusca, with descriptions or notices of forty-one hitherto undescribed species. Proceedings of the Zoological Society of London, 196 - 269, pls. 27 - 30." type="book chapter" year="1877">Abraham, 1877</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, based on morphology (
<bibRefCitation author="Dayrat, B." box="[337,469,898,922]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="1 - 403" refId="ref18248" refString="Dayrat, B. (2010) A monographic revision of basal discodorid sea slugs (Gastropoda, Opisthobranchia, Nudibranchia, Doridina). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 61 (1), 1 - 403, 382 figs." type="journal article" year="2010">Dayrat 2010</bibRefCitation>
); but now removed from synonymy due to a lack of morphological detail or molecular data for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Abraham" authorityYear="1877" box="[199,364,928,952]" class="Gastropoda" family="Dorididae" genus="Doris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nudibranchia" pageId="13" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="raripilosa">
<emphasis box="[199,364,928,952]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Doris raripilosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="14" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,998,1170]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,998,1024]" pageId="13" pageNumber="14">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Body covered with simple, rounded tubercles and/or complex branching tubercles; both stiffened with spicules. Broad foot, anteriorly notched. Labial cuticle armed with jaw rodlets. Radula composed of simple, hamate teeth with varying denticulation. Reproductive system composed of a granular prostate with two differentiated sections. Vagina unarmed. Penis armed with hooks. Granular accessory gland armed with an accessory spine (
<bibRefCitation author="Valdes, A." pageId="13" pageNumber="14" pagination="535 - 636" refId="ref21364" refString="Valdes, A. (2002) A phylogenetic analysis and systematic revision of the cryptobranch dorids (Mollusca, Nudibranchia, Anthobranchia). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 136, 535 - 636. https: // doi. org / 10.1046 / j. 1096 - 3642.2002.00039. x" type="journal article" year="2002">Vald√©s 2002</bibRefCitation>
). Head with two flat oral tentacles (present study).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
